1 banana
2 cherry

âœ… Hereâ€™s what happens:

    len(fruits) â†’ returns 3

    range(3) â†’ creates a sequence [0, 1, 2]

    The loop runs 3 times:

        When i = 0 â†’ prints fruits[0] â†’ "apple"

        When i = 1 â†’ prints fruits[1] â†’ "banana"

        When i = 2 â†’ prints fruits[2] â†’ "cherry"

ğŸ§© Example 2 â€” Accessing elements and their indexes

